list.name: Default
list.comment: No more need for the "cb" files, as now I just read the c and b files sequentially if necessary. Finally learned how to read files as resourceStreams so that a jar file for my program runs perfectly.

task.summary: Improved naming of some variables, and added a map of strings to countries and strings to CBBs for better display of options in the GUI
I learned what a controller is, and now the program is so much better. Initialization works correctly, no more "onMouseEnter" stuff. MainWindow adapts to whatever size it needs to be.

Eliminated one of the FXML files and controllers - now MainWindow is completely defined in code. Also, minusButton behaviour is slightly improved, and the MainWindow shows the country and CBB options.
Renamed currency files to their country code followed by "c" for coins, "b" for bills or "cb" for coins and bills.
